Damage from Hurricane Andrew is estimated at $ 20 billion , with $ 8 billion covered by insurance .
American insurers will take the brunt of the claims , but General Accident , the leading British insurer , expects claims to rise as high as $ 40 million .
Andrew tore through southern Florida , leaving 15 dead , power outages , and polluted water in his wake .
Homestead and the nearby air force base were flattened .
In Dade County , 250,000 people are homeless .
Andrew next smashed into Louisiana , killing two .
It missed the important oil refineries , but damaged crops and the oyster and alligator businesses .
The dollar sustained a similar assault .
